#  Linux & Windows Fundamentals

##  Overview
Understanding operating systems is essential for both offensive and defensive security.

##  What I Learned

### Linux
- Basic commands (ls, cd, cat, grep)
- File permissions and user management
- Navigating the file system

### Windows
- Basic system structure
- User accounts and permissions
- Security features

### Active Directory
- Basic concepts of domain, users, and groups
- Importance in enterprise environments

##  Command Line

- Windows CMD
- PowerShell basics
- Linux Shell usage

##  Key Takeaways

- Most real-world systems run on Linux or Windows
- Misconfigurations can lead to vulnerabilities
- Command-line skills are essential in cybersecurity


